node.text:
Lemon Ricotta Cake, a tender and moist lemony cake bursting with lemon flavor. This cake is drizzled with warm lemon syrup right after it is baked, to make the cake even moister.

After the cake is completely cooled, I spread a generous amount of lemon curd on top and Marshmallow frosting. I then slightly toast the marshmallow Frosting in an old-fashioned way.

This Lemon Ricotta cake is tender, moist, and incredibly delicious
What is not to love! This cake is definitely one of my top 5 favorite cakes to enjoy.

#cake #lemon #ricotta #yummy #sweettooth #canon #thefeedfeed #baking #recipes

node.text:
Two fluffy vanilla sponge cake layers, filled with a light and dreamy Greek Yogurt Strawberry & Passion fruit filling. The top is drizzled with a juicy passion fruit glaze.

This cake is what summer dreams are made of.

The whipped Yogurt frosting is light and so dreamy it is combined with fresh passion fruit pulp/juice and seeds and bright red strawberries especially when they are in season. This filling is so incredibly juicy and has the most amazing flavors of summer.
 

Instead of covering the cake with frosting, I decided to cover the second layer with a passion fruit glaze Instead, sometimes less is more.

The glaze is so juicy and bursting with passion fruit flavor a perfect match to the rest of the cake.
 

This is such a great combo, absolute homemade deliciousness!

I hope you fall in love with the cake and the flavors of this fluffy cake

#cake #spongecake #frosting #passionfruits #summervibes #strawberry #glazedcake #eeats #thefeedfeed #sweettooth #canon #macrophotography #video

node.text:
This is my favorite chocolate frosting, A light Cloud-like Chocolate frosting. It just melts in your mouth and it tastes like the most delicious chocolate mousse you have ever tasted.
This heavenly topping can be whipped up in a pinch.

This chocolate frosting is a dream to pipe on frosting, it is smooth it is silky, it is light in taste not too sweet and it is made without any butter. And best of all it takes just a few minutes to whip up.

This is my to-go frosting for my cupcakes, and it is perfect to fill or frost a cake.

node.text:
If you are looking for a show-stopping banana cheesecake, look no further.
This one features a crust made of frosties cereal, rather than predictable graham crackers but if you like your cheesecake to have a more classic crust use graham crackers instead.
On top of the crust is a dreamy banana cheesecake, that is super smooth in texture, it has tons of banana and vanilla flavor.

To get this delicious banana flavor in your cheesecake batter, I steep warm cream and vanilla bean paste together with sliced very ripe bananas in the fridge overnight. It is important you use very ripe bananas (those spotty brown bananas is perfect)  to get the ultimate banana flavor in your banana cheesecake

I hope You love this one as much as I do.

node.text:
When it comes to milkshakes, the banana flavor is my all-time favorite, I just love this nostalgic banana flavor and love incorporating the natural sweet banana flavor often into my frostings, cakes, cupcakes, and cheesecakes.
 

This Banana Milkshake - Whipped mascarpone is so delicious, it tastes just like an old-fashioned milkshake that you get at a diner, it is made with a banana-vanilla infused cream, using heavy cream, vanilla bean pod/seeds, and very ripe banana slices. I steep all these overnight in the fridge. resulting in the most amazing dreamy banana flavor in your frosting, tasting just like an old-fashion banana milkshake.

To get an intense banana flavor in your mascarpone it is so important you use very ripe bananas (those spotty brown bananas are perfect) to get the ultimate banana flavor.

The combination of banana-vanilla cream and mascarpone makes this frosting more stable/firmer and even more creamy and dreamy in taste, you just have to try it to understand how it tastes.

You can use this frosting as a filling in your cakes, or pipe on top of your cupcakes, or serve it on waffles, or on top of your ice cream, it is so delicious.

The bananas are sweet by themself, so you could easily make this frosting recipe sugar-free as it is just as delicious without the little amount of sugar I have added.

Juicy passion fruit & strawberry sweet rolls, these soft sweet rolls are just perfect for summertime.

These sweet buns are so fluffy, they are made with greek yogurt and are soft like pillows.

Each bun is baked with a generous amount of passion fruit curd in the center and fresh strawberries.

After the sweet rolls are baked until golden brown they are cooled and drizzled with a delicious and juicy passion fruit sugar glaze.

I hope you will fall in love with these sweet rolls, they are so delicious.

This Blackberry-Passion Fruit Cake is tender, fluffy, and exploding with blackberries and passion fruit flavor.

The cake is filled with a fresh blackberry Yogurt Frosting and the outside of the cake is decorated with a fresh passion fruit yogurt frosting.

The Blackberry Yogurt frosting that is in the middle of the cake is juicy, fresh, and so incredibly delicious in taste. The blackberries are cooked together with sugar, lemon zest, and fresh lemon juice to make them juicier, You get a wonderful vibrant purple fruitiness from the blackberries and a pleasant acidic note from the Greek Yogurt.

The passion fruit yogurt frosting that goes all over the cake is what dreams are made of, a light whipped yogurt frosting made with real vanilla seeds, combined with lots of passionfruit pulp, seeds, and juice. It is bursting with passion fruit flavors and is so dreamy in taste. You want to eat it by the spoonful.

These two flavors together between two fluffy sponge cake layers, Oh my a perfect summer cake.

If you love fruity summer cakes, and Scandinavia-style cakes  I  think You're going to fall in love with this cake.

node.text:
Fluffy strawberry summer cake

A soft white cake filled and covered with a fresh and creamy pale-pink strawberry cream, the cake is so fresh in taste and so fluffy and tender.

The perfect summer cake. especially now that the strawberries are in their peak season.
 

This cake is made with egg whites, a cake made with egg whites produces a much softer cake than a cake made with yolk or whole eggs.

This cake is also made without any butter or oil. however fat in a cake is important as it gives the cake moisture and richness. Instead of using butter, I use full-fat cream cheese, which gives a hint of flavor while simultaneously adding moisture and heavy cream 36 to 40%, both contain enough fat, both the fat of the cream cheese and heavy cream acts as a tenderizer in this cake batter, just as butter would do!

Making a white cake without butter means you can place this cake in the fridge and allow the cake to come to room temperature just before serving and it will still be soft and tender.

This fluffy white cake with fresh strawberries is like a taste of summer, I hope you fall in love with it.

Roasted strawberry puree captures the flavor of sun-warmed strawberries so well when they are in their peak season.
This frosting is made with fresh strawberries now that they are in season, roasting the strawberries first makes for a fresher and more concentrated strawberry puree and gives this roasted strawberry meringue frosting such a lovely and natural strawberry flavor.

Use this frosting to pipe onto your cupcakes or cover your cakes with, either way, it is delicious.

Make sure to make this frosting now that the strawberries are in season and at their peak, those gorgeous red strawberries will give you the best strawberry flavor in this frosting.
